issuesFound.explanation:
** The period buttons (`[data-period]`) in the pricing module are styled as a toggle group, but the code only adds/removes a CSS class (`CSS.active`). No `aria‑pressed` attribute is set, so screen‑reader users cannot tell which period is active.  
**Fix:** Update `_syncToggleState()` to set the attribute:  
```js
function _syncToggleState(period) {
  _periodBtns.forEach(btn => {
    const isActive = btn.getAttribute('data-period') === period;
    toggleClass(btn, CSS.active, isActive);
    setAttr(btn, 'aria-pressed', String(isActive));
  });
}
```  

